{
  "stem": "95.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "Everybody's going to be blonde eyes and-- blond hair and blue eyes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "You know, let's put everything on record.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "And that's what he did.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "And Serge Klarsfeld got a hold of the French record after the war, and he made a book out of it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And there are 76,000 names in this book-- 76,000 Jews who were deported only from France.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "And he gave me a book-- when I went to the World Gathering of the Jewish Survivors of the Holocaust in 1981 in Israel, and I was with him.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "Through a mutual friend, we went back to France together, to Paris together, and he said when we arrive in Pairs, give me a call, and I'll give you the book.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "And he gave me this thick book.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "And I was horrified by it, because it shows everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "It shows the day you were arrested, the day you were deported, the day you were born, where you were born, your first and last name, your profession-- it's all there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "Your nationality-- it's all there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "And I must tell you, the first time I flipped through those pages, it choked me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "I was crying because I saw names of all my childhood friends who lived in the same apartment buildings with their families.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "And I saw cousins, and I saw nephews, and nieces, and uncles, and aunts, and my mother, and my father, and sisters, and brothers-in-law, and me, with a dot in front of my name.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "It meant-- if there is a dot in the front of a name, it means that person came back.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "And you can flip those pages, and you see very few dots in front of names.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "And they look-- it shows everything.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
